h3. Summary
Loading an Agile board displays a Javascript error, "a.hasAttribute is not a function":
{noformat}
An exception has occurred in http://127.0.0.1:8080/s/389cefa756e99d05441edefd08894435-CDN/en_US-vyuule/64020/28/27dffb62c6d53c3687501abc152a3948/_/download/contextbatch/js/greenhopper-rapid-non-gadget,gh-rapid,atl.general,jira.project.sidebar,jira.global,jira.general/batch.js?jag_disabled_marketing=true&locale=en-US&isAdmin=true at 9194:277 --- Uncaught TypeError: a.hasAttribute is not a function
{noformat}
This only happens when using JIRA Service Desk 2.5

h3. Environment
* JIRA Agile 6.7.4
* JIRA Service Desk 2.5
* Chrome
* Safari

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Install JIRA Agile (6.7.4) and JIRA Service Desk (2.5);
# Access an Agile board;

h3. Expected Results
Board is displayed without problems.

h3. Actual Results
Javascript error is displayed at the top of the screen.

h3. Workaround
Downgrade JIRA Service Desk to version 2.4.3. Follow the steps below to achieve this:
# Stop JIRA;
# [Download JSD 2.4.3|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/download/plugins/com.atlassian.servicedesk/version/204030];
# Go to {{<JIRA_HOME>/plugins/installed-plugins}};
# Locate the {{jira-servicedesk-2.5.0.jar}} file and delete it (or save it somewhere else);
# Move the {{.jar}} file downloaded earlier (version 2.4.3) to the {{installed-plugins}} folder;
# Start JIRA;

In JIRA Agile, for scrum board when the plan mode is breaching the max viewable issues number. This error message will appear:
{code}
Maximum number of viewable issues (500) exceeded for this board.
{code}

However in the control chart itself it will only show the following message which is not meaningful at all:
{code}
"This chart cannot be displayed, There are either no issues on this board, or all the issues have been filtered out by the chart refinements."
{code}

The reason control chart is showing the above message is due to plan mode is breaching the max viewable issues number. Therefore it would be best if it could generate a more meaningful error message or display the same warning message in the control chart section.

When you run the below rest call, it will include all sprint which consist of *closed/deleted* sprint as well.

*Rest query*
{code}
http://localhost:8313/rest/greenhopper/1.0/sprintquery/3?include=FutureSprint=true&includeHistoricSprints=true&maxResults=2000
{code}
(i) Replace the {{http://localhost:8313}} and {{rapidViewId}} to the corresponding value.

*Result*
